        "convergence": "The moth colony is organized. Outer-ring moths seem to be scouts. Inner-ring moths are producers, sitting on the mana-crystal and apparently feeding directly from it. The queen—if there is one—is in the center, very large, very still, wings spread flat over the crystal. This is not an infestation. This is a factory."
